Welcome to the January 1996 issue of the GAC FLAK!

This issue contains the news that A4000T's have started shipping in the
USA; the official Power Amiga press release; the Design Works2.0 press
release; the conclusion of The Bench Master's interview with Jay Minor;
The Köln Computer Show Photo of the PowerUP processor card prototype
plus more.

For any potential advertisers: Please note that there is presently a
gaping hole in the midwestern US, centered around St. Louis, in which
there are no Authorized Amiga dealers. This hole covers the ENTIRE STATE
of Missouri. If you are near the St. Louis area and want our business,
please consider advertising in the GAC FLAK. You may contact me about
advertising in the manners described below.

William F. Maddock
Editor in Chief
